notes.body: Hello Anshul,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     I understand your query is related to the order #656836760307007488-29942. I see that the price of  MESACOL OD STRIP OF 15 TABLETS was updated from Rs. 571.88 to Rs.541.88 . Please accept my sincere apologies for the inconvenience caused.   We have initiated difference amount refund of Rs.216 on 8th December 2025. The refund will be credited to your payment source within 5-7 working days.   Also, I would like to inform you that the products listed in the app is not linked to the price. Thus, we share the estimated cost at the time of order placement, which can be either higher or lower than the actual price. We send you an SMS/push notification for the total discounted amount that needs to be paid as soon as your medicines are procured.   Sometimes, the MRP of the medicines may vary depending on the stock received by the chemist. This price variation will always be due to price changes by the medicine manufacturer. However, if the pricing on the medicine packaging differs from what is printed on the bill, please get back to us with the image of the medicine highlighting the batch number so that we can get the issue resolved.   For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.      Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!     Regards,  Tahera

Dear PharmEasy Support Team,

I am writing to report a recurring issue with my recent order placed on Tuesday, 2nd December 
(Order ID: 654878286588649472).

The item "Fin XI Strip Of 10 Tablets" was part of this shipment but was cancelled/not delivered.

I am facing the exact same situation as my previous order (Order ID: 621907987624
275968). Since a bank discount was applied to this order, if you process the refund to the original payment source, the bank will roll back the discount because the total order value has dropped. This results in me not receiving the refund in my bank account.

notes.body: Hello Suhas,     Greetings from PharmEasy!      I am sorry to inform you that your order #654878286588649472-88052 was cancelled due to the medicine that you added being unavailable with our Partner Retailer. I am sorry for the inconvenience caused to you.     Please note that at the time of placing the order, the requested medicine was available in limited quantity, and you were able to add medicines to the order. Once the medicine was added to your order, our Partner Retailer tried to arrange the medicine from every possible source. However, they could not arrange one. I apologize that we were unable to fulfil your medicine requirements for this order completely.     I request you to place a new order after 7 days for the required medicine. As our retailer restocks the medicines every 7 days. If the medicine is still unavailable, I would request you to reach us out to us. We will highlight your concern to the Partner retailer.     Regarding the refund amount, I have highlighted the issue to the Payments team. We will respond with the update as soon as we receive any from them.     I appreciate your patience in the meantime.     Regards,  Tahera
notes.body_html:
Hello Suhas,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

I am sorry to inform you that your order #654878286588649472-88052 was cancelled due to the medicine that you added being unavailable with our Partner Retailer. I am sorry for the inconvenience caused to you.

Please note that at the time of placing the order, the requested medicine was available in limited quantity, and you were able to add medicines to the order. Once the medicine was added to your order, our Partner Retailer tried to arrange the medicine from every possible source. However, they could not arrange one. I apologize that we were unable to fulfil your medicine requirements for this order completely.

I request you to place a new order after 7 days for the required medicine. As our retailer restocks the medicines every 7 days. If the medicine is still unavailable, I would request you to reach us out to us. We will highlight your concern to the Partner retailer.

Regarding the refund amount, I have highlighted the issue to the Payments team. We will respond with the update as soon as we receive any from them.

I appreciate your patience in the meantime.

Regards,
Tahera

Hello Vasireddy,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

I understand you wish to permanently delete your account with PharmEasy. We would be unable to delete the account from our database. 

We have to produce/show any or all transactions or interactions, past or present, when asked for by relevant Governmental authorities. 

Please note that once the account is deactivated, we are unable to process any request or reactivate the account.

Once your request has been processed in the system, our agent will call within 24 to 48 hours on a registered mobile number, and confirm if you have requested account deactivation. 

After verification, an OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number.  Once the OTP is verified, the agent will go ahead and deactivate your account  

Kindly confirm the so that we can proceed with the request.

Regards,
Tahera

Hello Manish Jagarwal,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with reference to the concern raised for order #657412919998091264-15734.
 
We have received an update from our logistics team that your order has been delivered. Also refiund of Rs.257.40/- against missing 1 qty of "LIPIDZ CREAM" is processed to your online source which will be credited within 5-7 working days.

Please accept my sincere apology for the inconvenience caused to you. We have shared the required feedback with the delivery agent and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!

Regards, 
PharmEasy

Dear Team,

My name is Ranjeet Kolase, and I am a student developer passionate about
solving healthcare challenges in both rural and urban communities. I
recently built an AI-powered healthcare application aimed at reducing
healthcare inequality by providing:

AI Symptom Checker

Awareness Hub (videos, audio guides, health documents)

Nearby Health Center Finder

Basic Digital Health Records

Community & Preventive Health Focus


The goal of the app is to help users—especially those with limited access
to healthcare—get quick, reliable preliminary guidance, understand health
risks, and easily locate the nearest support.

I believe this solution can complement your organisation’s vision and
existing digital health ecosystem. I would be grateful for an opportunity
to discuss whether this app could be:

Developed further under your guidance

roadmap whenever convenient.

Thank you for your time.
I look forward to hearing from you.

Warm regards,
Ranjeet Kolase
